  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: eac9ce3c2fc114c4c867216e6f3407f4, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Dialogue
  textComponent: {fileID: 1011044915}
  lines: []
  textSpeed: -2.03
  transitions: {fileID: 370433084}
  nextSceneName: Dinner_Testing
  fadeDuration: 1
  dialogueFirstTime:
  - "Dear, you may notice that we\u2019ll be eating different things for a while.
    I\u2019ve been laid off, so I won\u2019t be able to bring in your favorite delicious
    food unless I find it elsewhere."
  - 'What? Why were you laid off? '
  - "You see, the company I worked at hasn\u2019t been doing so well, and they don\u2019t
    have any more money to pay everybody, so they have to fire some people to make
    sure they can still exist."
  - "Why can\u2019t I eat my favorite food anymore??"
  - "Remember that if I\u2019m able to get it, I will always bring it for mama to
    prepare. Besides, some people have it worse than us. Remember that if you\u2019re
    ever unhappy with what we have."
  - But.. But the dads who still work at your job, I bet their families will eat
    good.
  - "I\u2019m sorry, but it wasn\u2019t your papa\u2019s decision\u2026 We still
    love you, but for a while, we can\u2019t show our love to you here at the dinner
    table as well as we could."
  - "That\u2019s not fair!"
  - "Papa\u2019s going to get food elsewhere, and I\u2019ll make it delicious, okay? "
  - "It\u2019s not fair."
  dialogueSecondTime:
  - Are you thinking about school?
  - Uh-huh. Are they going to make me take turns going there?
  - "Yes, honey. But that means you can play more games! You just have to make sure
    you don\u2019t play too much."
  - "I know, but I wanna play with my friends too! I only get to see them half of
    the time now. I don\u2019t even see \u2018em because their parents want to social
    distance."
  - "But their parents want social distance for a reason! Once it\u2019s over, they
    can come home here with us. Besides, you\u2019ve been playing with them in your
    online games, right?"
  - "It\u2019s not the same\u2026 but Oh-kay."
  dialogueThirdTime:
  - "So, how was your first day of your new grade? You\u2019re growing up to be strong."
  - It was great to see my friends again!
  - "That\u2019s so great."
  - "The new classes seem so difficult though. We already started learning all kinds
    of things I don\u2019t understand."
  - What do you need help on? Remember, whenever you need help, just ask me.
  - "But\u2026 You take so long to explain it, and it feels like you just make me
    work harder to understand it or do my homework."
  - 'Ha-hah. '
  - "Well, it\u2019s the same kind of thinking power that you might use when you
    do your homework. I\u2019m just helping you use it. You have everything you need."
  - "Well, it doesn\u2019t really feel like that."
  - How about after dinner, we help you with your first assignments?
  - "Ummm\u2026 No, I can do it on my own!"
  dialogueFourthTime:
  - What, this again?
  - "It\u2019s all I could find. You still need to eat regardless if you like it
    or not."
  - "I don\u2019t get it, why is always the same?"
  - "We haven\u2019t been able to decide what we eat under these conditions. So even
    if we can\u2019t eat our favorite food, we can\u2019t eat what we like, either."
  - "But why! It\u2019s been so long!"
  - "We have to make do. I know I\u2019ve been pretty upset by all the microwave
    meals."
  - "I mean, they\u2019re good, just..."
  - "I know. They don\u2019t taste the same from my cooking."
  - "Sometimes they\u2019re better than your cooking!"
  - "Don\u2019t say that to your mother!"
  dialogueFifthTime:
  - How was school today?
  - ...
  - "What\u2019s the matter?"
  - Did you have a bad day?
  - Someone told me I looked a little fat.
  - "A little fat? How could they say such a thing? You\u2019re not..."
  - "It\u2019s true though!"
  - "I\u2019m sorry, both of you. I have been, but the job market is difficult under
    these conditions. I\u2019ve applied to many, many jobs, but I\u2019ve been turned
    down on each of them."
  - When are you going to get a job! I hate this.
  - ...
  dialogueSixthTime:
  - "How\u2019s the job search?"
  - "Going as slow as usual. I\u2019m not going to miss this, but I never get out
    as often as these past few weeks. Maybe I\u2019ve lost some weight, actually."
  - "I don\u2019t think so. Have you seen yourself?"
  - Heh-heh.
  - "Hey, you don\u2019t have to laugh. That wasn\u2019t even funny."
  dialogueSeventhTime:
  - Good news, everyone.
  - What? Did you get my favorite food?
  - "I got a call back from a new company. They\u2019re interested, so I\u2019ll
    be having an interview. We\u2019ll be eating well again."
  - "I know you\u2019re excited, but you can\u2019t be too sure!"
  - Oh, I was hoping to eat decently for once...
  - But we will. Just wait a little bit more.
  - How much longer do we have to wait?
  - Hopefully, for not much longer.
